# Social Media Do’s and Don’ts

As college students, social media is a big part of our daily lives. It helps us stay connected, share ideas, and express ourselves. However, it is important to use these platforms responsibly because what we post online can affect our personal and professional image.

## Do’s
- Keep your profile clean and professional
- Share useful and meaningful content
- Respect others’ opinions and viewpoints
- Use privacy settings to control your information
- Think before posting anything online

## Don’ts
- Don’t share personal or sensitive information
- Don’t post offensive or inappropriate content
- Don’t spread fake news or unverified information
- Don’t engage in unnecessary arguments or hate comments
- Don’t ignore the long-term impact of your digital footprint

Using social media wisely can help build a positive online presence and create better opportunities in the future.
